The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Punters Corner -Easy win for Bourbon King
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Easy win for Bourbon King 
            SRIMAX      
	Trainer S. Ganapathys ward, Bourbon King, had an easy measure of his highly rated stablemate, Southern Empire, in the 1,600m Karnataka Cup, the star attraction in the Bangalore race card on Sunday. Jockey Y. S. Srinath partnered the four-year-old to victory. However, a heavy downpour soon after brought an end to the afternoons programme. Saturdays seven-event card was also truncated after the sixth race.  
